1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Graffe name change</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I have just seen the Graffe title change and if my reading of it is correct, the humor of it is certainly tempered with disappointment and sadness. I didn't find it funny. It was too true for that. The list of retiring Wizards on the message board is getting longer by the day. <br>
<br>
I don't remember that last time I got invited into a group and have been soloing for so long now that I no longer even bother trying. <br>
<br>
As a Wiz, I don’t want to have nukes that destroy mobs with a single cast. I do want to be of more use, do my share of damage in a group, and be of more use than just transport. And even with that, when was the last time anyone in their fifty’s really had a need for an Evac. Not enough for a Wiz to be wanted in a group I’ll tell you that.<br>
<br>
So this is the promised change to Wizard's is it! What we’ve been waiting for?  Redefinition of the class is more accurate. Well, I for one will not be getting the new spells, if this is all that is offered.<br>
<br>
If this sounds like just another Wizzie whine well, so be it. I’m sorry to say that this one has just about reached the end of the EQ road. I only got EQ to play a Wiz but VI has neutered us, showed itself unwilling to listen or act on complaints, which, by the way, were twice that of any other class when Absor asked for balancing suggestions. For me, these latest ‘changes’ have failed to give any hope that things will improve.<br>
<br>
I know that other classes have similar issues, Clerics for one but I would argue that Wiz’s are unique in their total reliance on mana and in their, at present, lack of real use in, and inability to get into a group. I could give a list of changes that I think are needed but I wont. Others have already covered that better than I could anyway<br>
<br>
Sorry about this rant, but I’m so angry and sad about this. I love this game for many reasons but I, and many of my Wizard friends are being forced out of it. After investing two years playing I believe I have a stake in this game and I thought I, and we all, had earned the right to be heard. I have tried to keep the faith and stay optimistic that VI would do something however, now, I believe they just don’t care and I feel stupid thinking they did. <br>
I did at one point at least have hope though.<br>
<br>
To finish, I would just like to thank Graffe for this site which, I have always found useful and essential viewing . <br>
